# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: This is NOT the main .env file!
#
# The actual .env file should be in the REPOSITORY ROOT, not in this config/ directory.
#
# Location: /opt/simplelogin/.env (or wherever you cloned the repository)
# NOT here: /opt/simplelogin/config/.env
#
# To create your .env file:
#   1. Go to the repository root: cd /opt/simplelogin
#   2. Copy the example: cp .env.example .env
#   3. Edit with your values: nano .env
#
# This config/ directory contains only Docker Compose configuration files:
#   - simple-login-compose.yaml
#   - postfix-compose.yaml
#   - traefik-compose.yaml
#
# These files reference the .env using: env_file: ${SL_CONFIG_PATH:-${PWD:-.}/.env}
# By default, this resolves to the .env file in the repository root.
# You can also place .env in the config/ directory if preferred.
